#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:1
msgid "DSO Integration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:3
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:5
msgid ""
"The Linked Data Explorer integrates with the **Digitaal Stelsel Omgevingswet "
"(DSO)** — the national catalogue and registry stack underpinning the Dutch "
"Environment and Planning Act. This integration lets process designers link "
"BPMN subprocesses directly to their authoritative DSO activiteit, browse the "
"Stelselcatalogus and werkzaamheden registry from inside LDE, and verify "
"references against live DSO data."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:7
msgid "The integration spans three DSO APIs:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:9
msgid ""
"**Stelselcatalogus** — the conceptual model (concepts, properties, value "
"lists)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:10
msgid ""
"**Zoekinterface** — search interface over werkzaamheden (the citizen-facing "
"tasks like \"boom kappen\")"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:11
msgid ""
"**RTR (Registratie Toepasbare Regels)** — the activity registry where each "
"authority's activiteiten and rule types live"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:13
msgid ""
"A toggle in Settings selects between the **pre-production** and "
"**production** DSO environments independently of the LDE environment."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:22
msgid "DSO environment toggle"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:24
msgid ""
"The DSO environment is set in **Settings → DSO environment** and persisted "
"to localStorage. It is independent of the LDE environment toggle — pre-"
"production LDE can talk to production DSO and vice versa, which matters "
"because some authority data is only available in one environment."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:26
msgid "LDE setting"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:26
msgid "API target"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:26
msgid "**Pre-production**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:26
msgid "`service.pre.omgevingswet.overheid.nl`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:26
msgid "**Production**"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:26
msgid "`service.omgevingswet.overheid.nl`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:31
msgid ""
"A coloured badge in the DSO Explorer header reflects the active environment "
"— amber for pre-production, green for production."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:40
msgid "Concepts tab"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:42
msgid ""
"Full-text search over the Stelselcatalogus. Returns concepts with their URI, "
"label, definition, and source. Useful for discovering the canonical "
"conceptual reference behind a citizen-facing term."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:46
msgid "Works tab — werkzaamheden"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:48
msgid ""
"Search the Zoekinterface for werkzaamheden (the citizen-facing tasks that "
"anchor a permit application — \"boom kappen\", \"Bed & Breakfast starten\"). "
"Autocomplete fires after two characters with 300ms debounce."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:50
msgid "Each result shows:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:52
msgid "The human-readable **omschrijving** (e.g. \"Bed & Breakfast starten\")"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:53
msgid ""
"The full **`functioneleStructuurRef`** URI — the pivot to STTR files for the "
"upcoming Phase 4 import"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:54
msgid "The short werkzaamheid URN"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:56
msgid ""
"Selecting a result opens a detail panel with the current version's metadata, "
"validity period, and full version history (each version showing start/end "
"dates and a \"current\" badge)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:63
msgid ""
"Default sort order is `meestGekozen` — the most-used Omgevingsloket "
"werkzaamheden appear first."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:67
msgid "Activities tab — activiteiten"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:69
msgid ""
"Browse the RTR (Registratie Toepasbare Regels) for activiteiten. The default "
"view lists recent activities; the **authority presets** (Lelystad, "
"Flevoland) filter the list by authority OIN (Organisatie-"
"identificatienummer) using `POST /activiteiten/_zoek` with "
"`bestuursorgaan.oin` as the body filter."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:71
msgid ""
"The date input above the list defaults to today; changing the date and "
"clicking **Load** re-fetches the authority list valid on that date."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:78
msgid ""
"Each activity card shows badges for the rule types declared on the activity:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:80
msgid "**Conclusie** — full DMN decision content available"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:81
msgid ""
"**Indieningsvereisten** — application requirements (questionnaire-style DMN)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:82
msgid "**Maatregelen** — measures (textual content, structured per maatregel)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:84
msgid ""
"These badges flag which downstream LDE assets can eventually be derived from "
"the activity in Phase 4 (DMN, form, document template)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:86
msgid "Activity Detail panel"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:88
msgid "Clicking an activity row opens the detail panel. It shows:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:90
msgid "omschrijving and full URN"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:91
msgid "bestuursorgaan (authority) — bestuurslaag, organisatieType, code, OIN"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:92
msgid "validity (begindatum / einddatum)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:93
msgid "parent activity link (if any)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:94
msgid "child activities — names fetched in parallel after the parent loads"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:95
msgid "rule types present, with download links"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:102
msgid ""
"If an activity is queried from the wrong DSO environment (e.g. trying to "
"view a production-only URN while the toggle is on pre-production), the "
"detail panel shows a clear \"not available in this environment\" message "
"rather than a raw 404."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:106
msgid "Linking a BPMN subprocess to a DSO activiteit"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:108
msgid ""
"The BPMN Modeler footer panel has a **DSO Activity** selector. Pasting a URN "
"and clicking **Verify** queries the live DSO RTR — on success, the panel "
"shows the omschrijving, authority, and a direct link to the public RTR "
"viewer. The URN is then persisted on the BPMN process element as "
"`ronl:dsoActiviteitUrn`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:115
msgid ""
"The verified URN survives saveXML round-trips and follows the same pattern "
"as other `ronl:` extensions (RoPA, language, organization)."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:119
msgid "Phase plan"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cdso-integration.md:121
msgid ""
"The integration is delivered in phases. The detailed plan, current status, "
"confirmed test anchors, and remaining work for each phase are tracked in "
"[DSO Integration Phase Plan]{1}. Phases 1–3 are live as of v1.5.3; Phase 4 "
"(STTR → DMN/form/document import) is the next development cycle."
msgstr ""

